The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 Principal PNB Mutual Fund has unveiled Principal Focused Advantage Fund, a diversified equity fund, which will invest in not more than six leading sectors at a time, with no sector constituting more than 25 per cent of the total portfolio. While the maximum number of sectors will be six, at any point of time the minimum will never be less than four. The fund is benchmarked against the S amp;P CNX Nifty and has a minimum application amount of Rs 5,000. The initial public offer will remain open till February 22, 2005.

 SBI Life Insurance has announced a 4 per cent interim bonus on pension policy?Lifelong Pensions for the financial year 2004-05. The bonus will be payable on all policies that were in force as on September 30, 2004. The interim bonus is paid in addition to the guaranteed return of 4 per cent per annum.

 UTI Mutual Fund has wound up the bonus option of UTI Growth and Value Fund as the scheme did not comply with Sebi?s December 31 deadline. All funds are required to have at least 20 investors with a single investor not accounting for more than 25 per cent assets of the fund. The redemption proceeds consequent to the winding up will be dispatched on February 9, 2005.




